Borno State Governor Kashim Shettima yesterday held an emergency extraordinary security meeting in Maiduguri over the resurgence of Boko Haram attacks. Six communities were reported to have been captured by the insurgents between Baga and Monguno in the Northern Borno Senatorial District in the last one week. After the closed-door meeting, a delegation was raised to deliver the resolutions to President Muhammadu Buhari. Representatives of all the security agencies and the Civilian Joint Task Force, hunters and the vigilante made separate presentations on the counter-insurgency overview. The Shehu of Borno, a representative of Borno elders, the three senators from the state and the speaker of the State House of Assembly as well as representatives of Baga, Kala-Balge and Maiduguri Metropolitan councils were to make brief comments and offer recommendations.